"a.接近的，毗连的 【英】 adj.接近的，毗连的( adjoining, contiguous, neighboring) 【记】 ad+jacent(to lie躺)→躺在附近→ 接近的； 【同】 n. adjacency(毗邻) adj. 接近的, 毗连的 = adjoining = contiguous = neighboring = abutting = approximal = bordering = conterminousthe city and adjacent suburbs 城市和附近的郊区adjacent garden plots 紧挨着的花园用地. 【记】ad朝向, jacent躺, 临近－在附近－接近的; adj = adj 形容词是连词－毗连的 【记】常见的adj 修饰语，是与要修饰的词连在一起，接近的 【相关】circumjacent 周围的, adjunct 附件,附属的 adjacent (adj.)  early 15c., from Latin adiacentem (nominative adiacens) ""lying at,"" present participle of adiacere ""lie at, border upon, lie near,"" from ad- ""to"" (see ad-) + iacere ""to lie, rest,"" literally ""to throw"" (see jet (v.)), with notion of ""to cast (oneself) down."""
